Text: By the way it's a reeseed from earlier
a little bit of everything from beginner level to advanced

I'm still seeding the other one, which worked fine for me (the second time - Bittornado failed, but Azureus took it like a champ in Linux).

And for those of you who are curious, you can view .chm files in *nix with "xchm" and I believe there's another one called "gnochm" if you use GNOME (which should work on KDE as well).
